Etymology. The species is named in honour of Hungarian Saint Kinga (or Kunigunda) (
1224–1292
) from the House of Árpád. She was the wife of Boleslaw Wstydliwy (= Boleslaw V the Chaste) (
1226–1279
), the ruling prince of Poland (
1243–1279
). She is the patron saint of Poland and Lithuania , and a strong historic tie between Hungary and Poland . The specific name symbolizes the comity of the two nations.
